result.execSummary:
The defendant Tammy L. Blank was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: Not ordered to pay DNA surcharge.

Maintain current employment or combination of education and employment equivalent to full time.  

Not quit employment without agent's approval.

AODA assessment and follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended.

No consumption or possession of any controlled substances except those prescribed to defendant and take prescribed medication exactly as directed to be taken.

Comply, if necessary, with any conditions per Monroe County Department of Human Services.

Comply with any rules, conditions and no contact orders per agent.

Defendant to pay supervision fees as determined by the Department of Corrections.

DEFENDANT ENTITLED TO 4 DAYS SENTENCE CREDIT IF PROBATION IS REVOKED.
